    "comment": "Rationale: Authors show, using a specific antibody, that importin alpha 2 is present in rat forebrain synaptosomal and PSD fractions. In primary hippocampal cultures, immunoreactivity of importin alpha 2 colocalized with the postsynaptic density marker PSD-95. Altogether, this data supports the localization of importin alpha 1 in the postsynaptic region.. Experimental description: From M&M and results sections:\n -Rabbit polyclonal antibodies were generated against mouse importin 2 (mPendulin).\n-Primary cultured hippocampal neurons were prepared from P0-P1 Black 6 mouse or Sprague-Dawley rat pups.\n-Synaptosome and postsynaptic density (PSD) fractions were prepared from adult rat forebrain.\n\n13/6/2017 Pim\n- There are two species that are featured in this paper (rat and mouse). I allowed annotation to mouse based on the confocal data.",
